<Values version="2.0">
  <record name="record" javaclass="com.wm.util.Values">
    <value name="node_type">record</value>
    <value name="node_subtype">unknown</value>
    <value name="node_nsName">com.ipaper.wmframe.core.edi.X12.V4010:T404DT</value>
    <value name="node_pkg">Framework_Core</value>
    <value name="node_comment">
This Draft Standard for Trial Use contains the format and establishes the data contents of the Rail Carrier Shipment Information Transaction Set (404) for use within the context of an Electronic Data Interchange (EDI) environment. The transaction set can be used to transmit rail-carrier-specific bill of lading information to a railroad. It is the initial tender of a shipment between a consignor and a rail carrier and can be used as notification of equipment release and/or a legal bill of lading.

Notes:
1/030 BX05 contains the Standard Carrier Alpha Code (SCAC) of the original roadhaul carrier receiving the shipment.
1/690 If the hazardous endorsement (LH204) is "NONE", then use of LH204 is mandatory. However, the receiver must consider it to be blanks when printing a paper document.
1/780 If the hazardous endorsement (LH204) is "NONE", then use of LH204 is mandatory. However, the receiver must consider it to be blanks when printing a paper document.
  </value>
    <value name="is_public">false</value>
    <value name="field_type">record</value>
    <value name="field_dim">0</value>
    <value name="nillable">true</value>
    <value name="form_qualified">false</value>
    <value name="is_global">false</value>
    <value name="originURI">is://com.ipaper.wmframe.core.edi.X12.V4010:T404</value>
